Description: AF ( Figs. 19 , 20 ) pygidium without lobes, plates, or gland spines; ducts few, minute, duct openings difficult to see. Apex of pygidium in most species with flat, spatulate margin and with 3–5 conspicuous longitudinal sclerotized ridges or folds. With 5-locular pores near anterior spiracles (but these apparently missing in 1 species,
B. longicauda
). Antenna with 1 seta. Adult female sclerotized at full maturity.
